      "title": "CLIP Text Encode (Positive Prompt)",
      "properties": {
        "Node name for S&R": "CLIPTextEncode",
        "cnr_id": "comfy-core",
        "ver": "0.3.45"
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "//from https://alidocs.dingtalk.com/i/nodes/EpGBa2Lm8aZxe5myC99MelA2WgN7R35y\nIn an oil painting style, a vast sea of sunflowers unfolds, their golden heads blooming brilliantly in the faint light of dawn or dusk. The impasto technique is prominently used, with bold, thick brushstrokes lending a powerful texture and vitality to the sky and petals. The deep blue of the sky creates a striking contrast with the bright sunflowers, cultivating an atmosphere that is both serene and hopeful. Swarms of bees dance and hover ceaselessly among the flowers, busily collecting nectar. These dynamic bees inject boundless energy and a sense of motion into the otherwise static painting, filling the entire scene with the vibrant life of summer and the joy of harvest.\n\n\n\n//This is the basic workflow. The custom node only uses gguf.\n//(https://github.com/city96/ComfyUI-GGUF)\n\n//Lora: 1.1v\n//https://huggingface.co/Kijai/WanVideo_comfy/tree/main/Wan22-Lightning\n\n//gguf:\n//https://huggingface.co/bullerwins/Wan2.2-T2V-A14B-GGUF/tree/main\n//https://huggingface.co/city96/umt5-xxl-encoder-gguf/tree/main\n\n//A high-LoRa strength of 1 seems to oversaturate and boring. \n//Reducing the strength seems to increase the movement, But unstable.\n//Try adjusting it to your liking. \n\n//By default, this creates a low-quality 480P preview. \n//If you like it, turn on the upscale group(You may need to update comfyui), do a V2V at 720P, and save it in high quality. \n//It takes about the same amount of time and quality as creating a 720P file from scratch, but it's nice to be able to preview it first.\n\n\n//This uses the subgraph of comfyui. If you have any node issues, please update the ComfyUI frontend.\n//TorchCompile can be ignored.\n"
      ],
      "color": "#232",
      "bgcolor": "#353"
    },
